Round 1 of the 2018 WGC – Mexico Championship will be hosted at the Chapultepec Golf Club in Mexico City, Mexico on Thursday 1st March. The 1st round tee times for the WGC – Mexico Championship golf tournament have been announced and the round is scheduled to start at 11:15 am. The 65 player strong field has been paired into 22 three-ball groups for the first two rounds of the WGC – Mexico Championship. The WGC – Mexico Championship round 1 tee times and player pairings. All tee times are local time. Groups starting from the 1st tee are listed first, followed by groups starting from the 10th tee.  The post 2018 WGC – Mexico Championship Round 1 Tee Times & Player Pairings appeared first on Golf and Course. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from News – Golf and Course. Click here to read the full text on the original website.